<p><strong>Film Credits:</strong><br/><br/></p> <p><strong>WE ARE GRAND CANYON</strong></p> <p>THIS FILM WAS ENVISIONED BY THE GRAND CANYON INTERTRIBAL WORKING GROUP REPRESENTING THE ELEVEN TRIBES TRADITIONALLY ASSOCIATED WITH THE GRAND CANYON</p> <p> <br/><strong>THANK YOU TO THE GRAND CANYON INTERTRIBAL WORKING GROUP</strong></p> <p>SHANANDOAH ANDERSON (SHIVWITS BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>TIM BEGAY (NAVAJO)</p> <p>RICHARD BEGAY (NAVAJO)</p> <p>CHARLEY BULLETTS (KAIBAB BAND OF PAIUTE INDIANS)</p> <p>DANIEL BULLETTS (KAIBAB BAND OF PAIUTE INDIANS)</p> <p>RONNIE CACHINI (ZUNI)</p> <p>CARRIE CANNON (KIOWA)</p> <p>CARMEN CLARK (SHIVWITS BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>MARCIE CRAYNON (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>DARREN DABODA (MOAPA BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>DON DECKER (APACHE)</p> <p>MAE FRANKLIN (NAVAJO)</p> <p>MICHAEL GCHACHU (ZUNI)</p> <p>AUTUMN GILLARD (CEDAR BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>RICHARD GRAYMOUNTAIN (SAN JUAN SOUTHERN PAIUTE)</p> <p>ANA JACKSON (YAVAPAI)</p> <p>STEWART B. KOYIYUMPTEWA (HOPI)</p> <p>LEE LOMAYESTEWA (HOPI)</p> <p>RICHARD POWSKEY (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>VINCENT RANDALL (APACHE)</p> <p>OCTAVIOUS SEOWTEWA (ZUNI)</p> <p>CARLETTA TILOUSI (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>DIANNA SUE WHITEDOVE UQUALLA (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>RONALD WADSWORTH (HOPI)</p> <p>BENNETT WAKAYUTA (HUALAPAI/HOPI)</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>A BRISTLECONE MEDIA PRODUCTION</strong></p> <p>A FILM BY RYAN M CHRISTENSEN</p> <p>IN COLLABORATION WITH</p> <p>GRAND CANYON INTERTRIBAL WORKING GROUP</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>PRODUCERS</strong></p> <p>JAN BALSOM</p> <p>MIKE LYNDON</p> <p>MINDY RIESENBERG</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>EDITORIAL CONSULTANT</strong></p> <p>TOMAS ARCEO</p> <p>VINCENT DIAZ (HUALAPAI/WASHOE)</p> <p>WEATHERCARROT</p> <p>KELKIYANA YAZZIE (NAVAJO)</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>CAMERA ASSISTANT</strong></p> <p>ANDY ROBSON</p> <p>KORY KIRCHNER</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>ADDITIONAL FOOTAGE</strong></p> <p>SUSAN ALZNER</p> <p>AERIAL FILMWORKS</p> <p>KEITH BYERS/SKYSHIP MEDIA</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>WITH SPECIAL APPEARANCES BY</strong></p> <p>SHANANDOAH ANDERSON (SHIVWITS BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>TIM BEGAY (NAVAJO)</p> <p>RONNIE CACHINI (ZUNI)</p> <p>CARMEN CLARK (SHIVWITS BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>AUTUMN GILLARD (CEDAR BAND OF PAIUTE)</p> <p>AUDRA JONES (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>JUSTIN JONES JR. (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>LORA JONES (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>ED KEABLE (NPS)</p> <p>ALBERT LAUGHTER (NAVAJO)</p> <p>LEE LOMAYESTEWA (HOPI)</p> <p>STERLING SELANA (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>ELYSSA SHALLA (NPS)</p> <p>KRISTOPHER SIYUJA (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>EDMOND TILOUSI (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>DIANNA SUE WHITEDOVE UQUALLA (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>JAMES UQUALLA (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>JORIGINE PAYA (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>JANELLE POWSKEY (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>RICHARD POWSKEY (HUALAPAI)</p> <p>VINCENT RANDALL (APACHE)</p> <p>OCTAVIOUS SEOWTEWA (ZUNI)</p> <p>CARLETTA TILOUSI (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>JAMES UQUALLA (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>RONALD WADSWORTH (HOPI)</p> <p>AVÉ WATAHOMIGIE-CORLISS (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>OPHELIA WATAHOMIGIE-CORLISS (HAVASUPAI)</p> <p>  </p> <p><strong>IN MEMORIUM</strong></p> <p>CHARLEY BULLETTS (KAIBAB BAND OF PAIUTE INDIANS) 1974-2020</p> <p>RONNIE CACHINI (PUEBLO OF ZUNI) 1965-2022</p> <p>VINCENT RANDALL (YAVAPAI APACHE NATION) 1940-2023</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>CHARLIE BULLETTS MEMORIAM FOOTAGE</strong></p> <p>JILL STAUROWSKY</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>PHOTOGRAPHS USED WITH PERMISSION FROM</strong></p> <p>GRAND CANYON NATIONAL PARK ARCHIVES</p> <p>HAVASUPAI TRIBE</p> <p>SHIVWITS BAND OF PAIUTE</p> <p>PIPE SPRINGS NATIONAL MONUMENT</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>\"We Made it, Honoring Current Life Beings\"</strong></p> <p>PERFORMED BY REX TILOUSI</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>\"North Wind Blowing\"</strong></p> <p>PERFORMED BY SHANAN MARTINEAU</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>SPECIAL THANKS</strong></p> <p>KIM BESOM</p> <p>MARIE BUCK<br/><br/>TODD CHRISTENSEN</p> <p>LAURA CROSSEY</p> <p>RADER LANE</p> <p>KARL KARLSTROM</p> <p>THERESA MCMULLAN</p> <p>JENNIFER O’NEILL</p> <p>MICHAEL QUINN</p> <p>ELYSSA SHALLA</p> <p>TODD STOEBERL</p> <p> </p> <p><strong>SPECIAL THANKS TO GRAND CANYON CONSERVANCY STAFF</strong> </p> <p>ALL FUNDING FOR THIS PROJECT WAS PROVIDED BY GRAND CANYON CONSERVANCY, OFFICIAL NON-PROFIT PARTNER OF GRAND CANYON NATIONAL PARK.</p> <p>\n</p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"VideoHero-text\">\n<a class=\"VideoHero-videoLink visuallyhidden\" href=\"/media/video/keyboard-shortcuts.htm\">Visit our keyboard shortcuts docs for details</a>\n<dl class=\"result-details wrapped\">\n<dt>Duration:</dt><dd>24 minutes, 8 seconds</dd>\n</dl>\n<p itemprop=\"description\">\"We Are Grand Canyon\" is a heartfelt film, welcoming visitors to Grand Canyon National Park from those who have called it home since time immemorial – Grand Canyon's 11 tribal communities.\nA project several years in the making, \"We Are Grand Canyon\" is a joint creation by the Intertribal Working Group, Grand Canyon National Park, and Grand Canyon Conservancy, and was filmed and edited by Ryan Christensen of Bristlecone Media.\nFilm Credits are listed in the transcript below the video player.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6277548\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6277548\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h4><strong>The Grand Canyon region has been home to Native people since time immemorial.</strong></h4>\n<p>The Grand Canyon is a place of immeasurable importance to Native people in the Southwest. The park shares boundaries with three federally recognized Tribes; a total of 11 federally recognized Tribes are traditionally associated with what is now Grand Canyon National Park. Park staff have been working with Tribal communities for more than 40 years, developing numerous innovative and collaborative tribal partnerships during that time. <br/>\n<br/>\nWe gratefully acknowledge the Native peoples on whose ancestral homelands we gather, as well as the diverse and vibrant Native communities who make their home here today.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6277554\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6277554\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Chevo-Medallion_SCALED_3.png?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Tribal Medallion representing the 11 traditionally associated Tribes of Grand Canyon\" src=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Chevo-Medallion_SCALED_3.png?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Tribal Medallion-Scaled\"/>\n</picture>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2>Traditionally Associated Tribes</h2>\n<p>There are 11 Tribes that have historic connections to the lands and resources now found within Grand Canyon National Park.<br/>\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Havasu'baaja</strong> <a href=\"https://www.theofficialhavasupaitribe.com/\">Havasupai Tribe</a> – AZ </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.hopi-nsn.gov/\">Hopi Tribe</a> – AZ </li>\n<li><strong>Hwal'bay</strong> <a href=\"https://hualapai-nsn.gov/\">Hualapai Tribe</a> – AZ</li>\n<li><strong>Nungwu</strong> <a href=\"https://kaibabpaiute-nsn.gov/\">Kaibab Band of Paiute Indians</a> – AZ </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lvpaiutetribe.com/\">Las Vegas Paiute Tribe</a> – NV   </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.moapabandofpaiutes.com/\">Moapa Band of Paiute Indians</a> – NV  </li>\n<li><strong>Diné</strong> <a href=\"https://www.navajo-nsn.gov/\">Navajo Nation</a> – AZ\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://navajonationparks.org/\">Navajo Nation Parks &amp; Recreation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.utahpaiutes.org/\">Paiute Indian Tribe of Utah</a> – UT </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sanjuanpaiute-nsn.gov/\">San Juan Southern Paiute Tribe</a> – AZ  </li>\n<li><strong>A:shiwi </strong><a href=\"https://www.ashiwi.org/\">The Pueblo of Zuni</a> – NM</li>\n<li><strong>Yavap'e - Nṉéé</strong> <a href=\"https://yavapai-apache.org/\">Yavapai-Apache Nation</a> – AZ  </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7119648\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7119648\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"Two maps side by side showing the traditional homelands of Grand Canyon's 11 associated tribes and their current reservation lands today.\" src=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/2023-tribal-maps-1ayers-copy.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"Traditional lands and current land allocation maps of the 11 associated tribes of the Grand Canyon region.\"/>\n<figcaption>The map on the left shows approximate locations of the traditional homelands of the 11 Tribes that have cultural connections to Grand Canyon. The map on the right show current Tribal reservations as well as the boundary of Grand Canyon National Park. <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS, Adapted from Stephanie Smith, 2020</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7120454\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7120454\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Working with Indigenous communities</h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7120452\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7120452\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/getinvolved/tribal-vending-opportunities.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/getinvolved/tribal-vending-opportunities.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Vendors sit behind a table as visitors look at handicrafts and jewelry\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/2DAFD770-9864-696C-A7502710CE42E946.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/2DAFD770-9864-696C-A7502710CE42E946.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/2DAFD770-9864-696C-A7502710CE42E946.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Native Vending and Demonstration Program</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Discover the rich Native American culture at Grand Canyon National Park through our diverse tribal vending and demonstration programs.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/desert-view-cultural-demonstration-program.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/planyourvisit/desert-view-cultural-demonstration-program.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A man sits at a table with silver works and a display of silver jewelry \" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/7F91BDB7-E516-CFD5-C5E1FECE01159330.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/7F91BDB7-E516-CFD5-C5E1FECE01159330.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/7F91BDB7-E516-CFD5-C5E1FECE01159330.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Cultural Demonstration Program</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Watch artists from traditionally associated tribes practice traditional and modern crafts and share their living cultural traditions.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://www.grandcanyon.org/our-work/current-priorities/desert-view/?cid=14762092235&amp;agid=130592060147&amp;mt=&amp;dev=c&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQiArt6PBhCoARIsAMF5wajq5O-fnWqP2rLwdr83kncdJUbMZEe-rSOLZfwbTvmyu-rPuI1t9xAaArqkEALw_wcB\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://www.grandcanyon.org/our-work/current-priorities/desert-view/?cid=14762092235&amp;agid=130592060147&amp;mt=&amp;dev=c&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQiArt6PBhCoARIsAMF5wajq5O-fnWqP2rLwdr83kncdJUbMZEe-rSOLZfwbTvmyu-rPuI1t9xAaArqkEALw_wcB', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A group of people standing in front of a stone tower with Grand Canyon behind them.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/21B69BB3-DAE5-DAC6-C81CA4A034079782.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/21B69BB3-DAE5-DAC6-C81CA4A034079782.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/21B69BB3-DAE5-DAC6-C81CA4A034079782.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Desert View Intertribal Heritage Site</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">See the many exciting changes in store for the future of Desert View, including a new Tribal-run welcome center and improved paths. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7763731\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7763731\">\n<h3>Grand Canyon National Park Tribal Engagement Report</h3>\n<div class=\"StoryMap__Intro\">A biennial report highlighting Grand Canyon National Park tribal programming in 2022-2023.</div>\n\n<div class=\"StoryMap__Link\" style=\"padding-bottom: 20px;\"><a alt=\"Link to view the story map in full screen mode.\" href=\"https://www.nps.gov/maps/stories/grand-canyon-national-park-tribal-engagement-report.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"View the full-screen version of this interactive content.\">View full screen &gt;</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7141118\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7141118\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Additional Resources</h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6277666\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6277666\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/history/native-cultures/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/history/native-cultures/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Prehistoric granaries along the Colorado River\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F371FE23-EDF0-F5C0-A60010C949F3BEB4.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F371FE23-EDF0-F5C0-A60010C949F3BEB4.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F371FE23-EDF0-F5C0-A60010C949F3BEB4.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Associated Tribes of Grand Canyon</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Learn more about Associated Tribes of Grand Canyon on Arizona State University's Nature, Culture, and History at Grand Canyon website.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/arch.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/arch.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\" Archaeological Resources\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F4184063-F76A-BAA3-B04096353738CC6B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F4184063-F76A-BAA3-B04096353738CC6B.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F4184063-F76A-BAA3-B04096353738CC6B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Archaeological Resources</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Humans have present on the Grand Canyon landscape for up to 12,000 years. Find out what archaeologists have found inside the park.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/desert-view.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/planyourvisit/desert-view.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A small single-story stone building with an entry on the right. Sign reads: Tusayan Museum. \" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F3B6D0B8-E977-EE63-69B455C916657211.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F3B6D0B8-E977-EE63-69B455C916657211.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F3B6D0B8-E977-EE63-69B455C916657211.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Tusayan Pueblo and Museum</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">CLOSED FOR THE WINTER. Visit this 800-year-old ancestral Puebloan site and learn about people who called Grand Canyon home. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://www.grandcanyontrust.org/advocatemag/fall-winter-2020/voices-grand-canyon\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://www.grandcanyontrust.org/advocatemag/fall-winter-2020/voices-grand-canyon', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Tribal members hold a ceremony near the Grand Canyon Visitor Center\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F62B5D84-D55C-871D-51DA110C702652D1.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F62B5D84-D55C-871D-51DA110C702652D1.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F62B5D84-D55C-871D-51DA110C702652D1.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">The Voices of Grand Canyon </div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Visit Grand Canyon Trust's website to see what it means to call the Grand Canyon home. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://arizonaindiantourism.org/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://arizonaindiantourism.org/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Cellist YoYoMa stands near the canyon with tribal member, Jim Enote \" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F6F78BA8-F8D3-B87F-1AB7A9B93DE3B968.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F6F78BA8-F8D3-B87F-1AB7A9B93DE3B968.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F6F78BA8-F8D3-B87F-1AB7A9B93DE3B968.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Arizona Native Tourism</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Arizona American Indian Tourism Association promotes the development of Indian Tourism while respecting the cultural integrity of tribes</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://www.aianta.org/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://www.aianta.org/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"The Navajo Bridge spans across the Colorado River. \" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F68A2688-FF4A-09A9-4EFE7E7D85FAFA00.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F68A2688-FF4A-09A9-4EFE7E7D85FAFA00.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/F68A2688-FF4A-09A9-4EFE7E7D85FAFA00.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Partnering with AIANTA</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The American Indian Alaska Native Tourism Association serves as the national voice for American Indian nations engaged in cultural tourism.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: March 10, 2026</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_828654\"> </div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
